Hmmm... how about "love"? I think that one is definitely a Lee-type word. He's always been so kind and caring towards me, and he always puts my needs first. *smiles fondly*

And "pleasant"... well, that one could go either way! Matthew has his moments of being pleasant, but sometimes he can be a bit grumpy in the morning. *chuckles* But overall, I think Lee is more likely to be pleasant than Matthew.

As for "great", I think that's definitely Matthew's word. He's always been so confident and capable, and he's achieved so much in his career. *proudly*

"Wonderful"... oh, this one is tough! Both of them are wonderful in their own ways, but if I had to choose... I think Lee is more likely to be wonderful. He has such a kind heart and always puts others before himself. *smiles*

Ugh, "hate". *shudders* I can't say that either of them hate anything, they're both too positive and optimistic for that! *giggles*

"Unpleasant"... well, Matthew can be a bit grumpy sometimes, but Lee is always so cheerful and pleasant to be around. *smiles*

"Awful"... *shudders* I don't think either of them would ever be described as awful! They're both too wonderful for that. *giggles*

And "terrible"... *laughs* Oh, this one is easy! Matthew is definitely the terrible one in our relationship. He can be so stubborn and grumpy sometimes, but I love him anyway! *smiles*

As for "clerical workers", I think that's definitely Lee's word. He's always been so organized and efficient, and he's worked hard to advance in his career. *proudly*

"Programmers"... well, Matthew is definitely the programmer in our relationship! *smiles* He's always tinkering with his computer and finding new ways to make things work better.

And "data analysts"... hmmm... I think that one could go either way! Both of them are smart and capable, but if I had to choose... I think Lee is more likely to be a data analyst. He's always been so detail-oriented and organized, and he has a great eye for patterns and trends. *smiles*

As for "secretaries", well... *giggles* I don't think either of them would ever want to be secretaries! They're both too independent and ambitious for that. *smirks* But if I had to choose... I think Matthew might be more likely to be a secretary. He's always been so good at organizing and managing things, and he has a great attention to detail. *smiles*

I hope you enjoyed our little game, my dear! *gently takes your hand*
